sections.heading: Deposit of material on wharf or quay regulated.
sections.text: 309.02 Deposit of material on wharf or quay regulated.—It is not lawful for any person to deposit or cause to be deposited on any wharf or quay, any ballast, stone, earth, or like material, except such wharf or quay may be so secured as to prevent such ballast or other material from washing into the waters of the harbor. History.—s. 3, ch. 3142, 1879; RS 937; GS 1291; RGS 2461; CGL 3870.
